<html><head><title>Smedley Comments on Player Conduct</title></head><body class="newsbody" ><div class=newbody><h2>EverQuest Vault -- EQ </h3><h3>Smedley Comments on Player Conduct</h3><p>John Smedley "Smed" has a short <a herf="http://stationblog.wordpress.com/2006/02/16/virtual-jail/">piece</a> on how he feels about people's rights in-game and out and the conduct of GMs in the game.<br><br>"...What doesn’t get the media or the rant sites excited (unfortunately so, I think) are the vast majority of times GMs get things right, including dealing with inappropriate behavior quietly, behind the scenes, the way it should happen. I wish people didn’t think that because they’re in the privacy of their own homes and they are “anonymous” that they can act any way they want, but that’s just a fact of life in the MMO world. "</div><p><div classs=copyright><font face=arial size=2 color=#959595>News Story from EverQuest Vault -- EQ <br>News Date: Friday, 17 February, 2006<br>Link: <a href="http://eqvault.ign.com/fullstory.php?id=15071">http://eqvault.ign.com/fullstory.php?id=15071</a><br>Printed On: Tue Jun 13 16:31:39 PDT 2006<br>©2005 IGN Entertainment</font></span>